Two trolley pushers were arrested at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport on Friday after stealing thousands of dollars from a customer. According to the DCI, Kennedy Ochieng (22) and Kevin Ogega (25) are both employees of Tropical Promoters - a company that offers trolley services at JKIA. The DCI did not disclose how much the two stole, but said the amount was recovered. "Today we arrested Kennedy Ochieng, 22yrs, and Kevin Ogega, 25yrs, for stealing thousands of Dollars belonging to a passenger. All the cash recovered after a search," reads the tweet. Click here for the latest political news